OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F379A1780078265
OL,3,CFake England shirts seized at car boot
OL,4,Ccould have caught fire
OL,6,FA huge haul of fake England shirts
OL,7,Fcould have caught fire while people
OL,8,Fwere wearing them, as well as damaging
OL,9,Fskin because they contained harmful
OL,10,Fchemicals.
OL,12,FThe fake football kits were on offer
OL,13,Fat a car boot sale in Leicestershire.
OL,15,FTrading standards officers say fake
OL,16,Fshirts are usually 100% polyester,
OL,17,Fwhich is highly flammable, and some
OL,18,Fcontain harmful dyes or chemicals.
OL,20,FAn estimated half of all England
OL,21,Fshirts worn by fans are counterfeit.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G1/3
