OL,3,CFake England shirts seized at car boot
OL,4,Ccould have caught fire
OL,6,FOne man has been arrested and bailed
OL,7,Ffollowing an investigation at local
OL,8,Fcar boot sales.
OL,10,FOfficial Nike jerseys regularly exceed
OL,11,F#80 whilst a fake can be picked up for
OL,12,Fbetween #15 and #20, and police
OL,13,Festimate the damage to the legitimate
OL,14,Fmarket at around #400,000.
OL,16,FReporting History sees journalists
OL,17,Fjoin News At Ten anchor Tom Bradby to
OL,18,Frevisit their remarkable on-the-day
OL,19,Freports of the defining events of the
OL,20,Fmodern age. Listen to the episodes
OL,21,Fbelow...
